message:
Ignore empty parent components when ensuring directories exist

RunStore::open, sync::save_cursor, sync::import_inner, and
tty_audio::transcode_mulaw_to_wav all follow the same pattern when
preparing to write to a user-supplied path:

    if let Some(parent) = path.parent() {
        fs::create_dir_all(parent)?;
    }

That is subtly wrong when the caller passes a bare filename like
`run.db` or `out.wav` — `Path::parent()` returns `Some("")` in that
case, and `create_dir_all("")` on Linux then fails with
`No such file or directory (os error 2)` because the empty string is
not a valid path. Callers that wanted "create-in-CWD" got a hard
error instead, which showed up as a test-only regression on
tty_audio::transcode_mulaw_to_wav for relative output paths and was
worked around in practice by always feeding absolute paths.

Fix is mechanical and matches what we already do in fsqlite-vfs::
host_fs::write_file: guard the create_dir_all on `parent` being both
Some AND non-empty. For RunStore and the two sync helpers the check is
inlined with a let-chain; tty_audio gets a small `ensure_parent_dir`
helper so the transcode path and any future writers can share a
single implementation:

    fn ensure_parent_dir(path: &Path) -> FwResult<()> {
        let Some(parent) = path.parent() else {
            return Ok(());
        };
        if parent.as_os_str().is_empty() {
            return Ok(());
        }
        fs::create_dir_all(parent)?;
        Ok(())
    }

A tty_audio unit test covers the empty-parent case directly:

    #[test]
    fn ensure_parent_dir_ignores_empty_parent() {
        let path = Path::new("out.wav");
        ensure_parent_dir(path).expect("empty parent should be ignored");
    }

so we catch any regression without having to reach into the larger
mulaw→wav transcode path. The test module grows a `use std::path::Path`
and a re-export of `ensure_parent_dir` to pull the private helper
into scope.

No behavioral change for absolute paths — they always have a
non-empty parent, so they take the same create_dir_all branch as
before.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

